SIMPLE: uproot
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uproot
<hw>Up*root"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To root up; to
tear up by the roots, or as if by the roots; to remove utterly; to
eradicate; to extirpate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Trees <qex>uprooted</qex> left their place.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At his command the <qex>uprooted</qex> hills retired.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uprouse</ent>⟦br⟧
